hopobject.body: I didn't go to university fr.lcn-steroid.com Mr. Summers, a former Treasury secretary, has for several weeks been viewed as one of two top candidates to lead the Federal Reserve after current chairman Ben Bernanke’s second term ends in January. But resistance to Mr. Summers could tilt the balance in favor of Federal Reserve Board Vice Chairwoman Janet Yellen, whom many Democrats have lobbied the president to choose instead, or to other candidates who have been out of the glare of the very public race.
